{
  "stem": "14613.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, one of the worst things was when he said, all children have to be sent out from ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Old people had to be sent out from ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Sick people had to be sent out from ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the people that worked for the-- for Rumkowski, whether that was the administration and the police department, or anything else, they were, in a way, exempt from the aussiedlung, from being moved out from ghetto.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there became more and more friction between the population and the-- and the administration of ghetto.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It reached the point where-- where the starvation was such that it was a complete distrust to the-- to the-- to the leadership.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, in a way, we always started to think that Rumkowski, as the head of it, became so powerful that he became like the King of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this also created a tremendous resentment.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He would drive in the horse and buggy-- beautiful horse and buggy-- with some of his people surrounding him, and well-fed, looking beautifully.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This, by itself, when-- when you are hungry, and you're starving, and your family is starving, and you look at people so well-fed, yet supposedly that should be in the same condition, it creates much more problems than-- than normally you can foresee.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this is what was happening in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There was the so-called privileged class, and the underprivileged class.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in a way, we were a little privileged, too, because we were able to get what we call [NON-ENGLISH], which means a piece of land.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And a piece of land, which basically my brother and myself, we-- we-- we became farmers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We have learned how to cultivate the land.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
